Origin of the name Quinn: Derived from the Irish surname O' Quinn which is from the Gaelic O' Cuinn (descendant of Conn). The name is derived from conn (wisdom, reason, intelligence).

Quinn Name Meaning, Origin & Details

Meaning: Signifies queen Details: From the Irish Cuinn, a form of Conn which means "chief" or "wise" in Gaelic. Gender: For both boy and girl, unisex, transgender, neutral gender Origin: Gaelic Religion: Christian Suitable for: Unisex / Gender neutral Hardness: Easy to pronounce, Quinn is a short name Uniqueness: It is a common name Short & Easy: Yes Syllables: 5 Letters and 1 Words
